The Jouberts have been filming, researching and exploring Africa for over 30 years. CAPE TOWN Award-winning filmmakers and wildlife conservationists Beverley and Dereck Joubert were attacked by a buffalo in Okavango.The Jouberts have been filming, researching and exploring Africa for over 30 years. They have founded the Big Cats Initiative, together with National Geographic, which currently funds 39 grants in 17 countries for the conservation of big cats.Dereck made the announcement of the attack via their social media page, saying they were charged by a buffalo and Beverly was seriously injured following the incident. She is currently in a stable condition in hospital.Thoughts and prayers go out to Beverely and Dereck Joubert who were in a buffalo attack. Get well soon guys and keep up the fantastic work!